  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "UIUX Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Collaborate with design and development team to define and implement innovative solutions for the product direction, visuals and user experience.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with UX/UI design team to create compelling user experiences on mobile apps and websites.</li>\n  <li>Conduct user research and evaluate user feedback.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with the stakeholders to make effective decisions.</li>\n  <li>Write reports based on findings and feedbacks received from user research.</li>\n  <li>Assist in creating wireframes and mock-ups.</li>\n  <li>Proactive and have a sense of process ownership.</li>\n  <li>Proven ability to manage multiple design requests in a timely fashion, with competing priorities and deadlines</li>\n  <li>Employ design thinking and work with leadership in design planning, developing product strategies, establishing goals and execution plans</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>​</strong></p>\n<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma in Art/Design, Creative Multimedia/ Advertising/ Media, Computer Science/ Information Technology or equivalent.</li>\n  <li><strong>Minimum 3 years</strong> experience in <strong>UX/UI Design</strong> and familiar with <strong>visual design</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding and passion for the customer usage journey.</li>\n  <li>Skills in <strong>Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator, Sketch</strong> or other visual and icon design and wireframing tools will be an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Good English oral and written communication skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em><strong>Please attached your interactive portfolio in resume.</strong></em></p>",
